Our goal is to forecast annualized real GDP growth at the quarterly frequency at horizons that range from 15 days before the official release to approximately a year. The baseline specification that we consider is

$Ya = an + NhSd-h + Xanh + ed-h,$

where:
• $Yd$ represents the GDP growth for quarter t that is released on day d; we use two indexes to track both the calendar time of the variable as well as the irregular release dates;
• $Sd-h$ denotes a confidence or sentiment indicator available at the time the forecast is made on day d - h, that is, h days before the official release date, d; the goal here is to accurately track the real-time flow of information that is available to forecasters;
